    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, quarter them lengthways and cut into batons</p><p>Drain your <strong>beetroot</strong> in a colander over the sink</p><p>Chop the <strong>drained beetroot</strong> into wedges</p><p>Place the <strong>carrot</strong> <strong>batons</strong> and <strong>beetroot</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> on a baking tray</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crumble your <strong>Greek cheese </strong>and your <strong>cumin seeds </strong>over the beetroot and carrots, then drizzle with your <strong>honey</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the carrots are slightly tender with some crunch</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a medium pan over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and toast for 3 min or until slightly darkened and starting to pop</p><p>Set the toasted pumpkin seeds aside until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix well \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges for garnish</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-rainbow-salad-with-greek-cheese-and-lime/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted beetroot</strong>, <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>Greek cheese </strong>over the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>dressing</strong> and garnish with your <strong>toasted pumpkin seeds </strong>and<strong> lime wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
